  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How do you block someone on Quora?",
  "response": "Blocking someone on Quora is a straightforward process. Here's how you can do it:\n\n### On the Quora Website:\n1. **Visit the Profile**: Go to the profile of the user you want to block.\n2. **Click the Three Dots**: On their profile page, click the three dots (\u2022\u2022\u2022) located below their profile information.\n3. **Select \"Block [Username]\"**: From the dropdown menu, choose the option that says \"Block [Username].\"\n4. **Confirm the Block**: A confirmation prompt will appear. Click \"Block\" to confirm.\n\n### On the Quora Mobile App:\n1. **Visit the Profile**: Open the profile of the user you want to block.\n2. **Tap the Three Dots**: Tap the three dots (\u2022\u2022\u2022) located in the top right corner of their profile.\n3. **Select \"Block [Username]\"**: From the menu, select the option that says \"Block [Username].\"\n4. **Confirm the Block**: A confirmation prompt will appear. Tap \"Block\" to confirm.\n\n### What Happens When You Block Someone:\n- **Content Visibility**: The blocked user will no longer see your content, and you won't see theirs.\n- **Notifications**: You won't receive notifications from the blocked user.\n- **Messages**: Any previous messages or interactions will remain, but you won't be able to interact further.\n\n### Unblocking Someone:\nIf you ever want to unblock someone, you can do so by visiting their profile and selecting the \"Unblock\" option from the same menu.\n\nThis helps maintain your privacy and ensures a more positive experience on the platform.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
